  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Marketing Executive & Receptionist",
  "description": "<p>We are a modern dental clinic passionate about delivering quality care and creating a positive experience for our patients. As part of our growth, we are looking for a dynamic individual who can contribute both to our front-desk operations and to building our online presence through creative marketing.</p><p><br /></p><p>We are located in Wheelock Place, Orchard Road. </p><p><br /></p><p><strong>Role Overview</strong></p><p>This is a dual-role position that combines digital marketing responsibilities(70%) with patient-facing receptionist duties(30%). You will be the creative force behind our clinic’s social media presence while also ensuring patients feel welcomed and cared for when they visit us.</p><p><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong><br /><br /><em>Marketing & Social Media</em></p><p>Manage and grow the clinic’s social media platforms (Instagram, Facebook, YouTube, TikTok, Xiao Hong Shu).</p><p>Create engaging content, campaigns, and posts to build brand awareness and patient engagement.</p><p>Monitor analytics and suggest improvements to increase reach and conversions.</p><p>Coordinate and design marketing collateral (brochures, posters, patient materials).</p><p>Support marketing initiatives such as promotions, events, or collaborations.<br /><br /><em>Reception & Front Desk Duties</em></p><p>Welcome and assist patients with professionalism and warmth.</p><p>Manage appointment scheduling, phone calls, and patient inquiries.</p><p>Process payments, billing, and administrative paperwork.</p><p>Ensure smooth day-to-day front-desk operations on assigned days.<br /><br /><strong>Requirements</strong></p><p>Diploma in Marketing, Communications, or related field preferred.</p><p>Prior experience in social media management and/or marketing is an advantage.</p><p>Good design sense and familiarity with Canva/Photoshop or similar tools.</p><p>Friendly, well-spoken, and professional with strong interpersonal skills.</p><p>Organised, proactive, and able to multi-task across marketing and reception duties.</p><p>Previous experience in dental/medical reception is an advantage but not required (training provided).<br /><br /><strong>What We Offer</strong></p><p>A supportive team environment.</p><p>Opportunities to grow in both marketing and healthcare administration.</p><p>Exposure to healthcare industry branding and patient engagement strategies.</p><p>Competitive salary package with staff dental benefits.</p>",
